  <h1>
   string_letters
  </h1>
  With this function you can remove all characters that are not classed as letters. This is handy for preventing people from entering unwanted characters into a text entry (like entering "#" to force a new line).
  <span>
   NOTE
  </span>
  This function only detects and returns the 26 letter English alphabet from A - Z (upper or lower case).
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">string_letters(string);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      string
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        String
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The string to convert to letters.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 String
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">username = string_letters(username);
</code></pre>
  The above code will set the "username" variable to only hold the
  <i>
   letter
  </i>
  characters of the original string (id the original string was "MacSw33ny" the returned string would be "MacSwny").
 </body>
</html>